  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe water for 142 children in Argentina</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will build a rainwater harvesting system with a 52,000-liter water tank that will serve the demand for water for consumption by the educational community of the Kindergarten and Nursery N 193, in the province of Chaco, and we will also provide school training in 15 communities in Argentina to promote the right to water. It will also train its teachers and families in good practices for the water management as a contribution to the health and hygiene of the community.</narrative>
  </description>
